learning_outcomes.en:
On completing the course a student will be able to:
- understand the essence and main concepts relating to evidence-based practice in the area of health and well-being;
- understand the essence of effective preventions and interventions in the area of subsistence abuse, HIV/AIDS, eating and behavioral disorders, and bullying behavior of children and youth; 
- critically evaluate the available research evidence in the area of evidence-based practice of children and youth health and well-being.
